,"label":"2Tm 1:7","book":"2Ti","chapter":1,"verse":7,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" in him and he will hear a rumor and return to his own land, where I will cause him to fall by the sword.’” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 37:36–38","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":36,"letter":"f"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Nm 5:14","book":"Num","chapter":5,"verse":14},{"label":"Is 19:14","book":"Isa","chapter":19,"verse":14},{"label":"Hs 4:12","book":"Hos","chapter":4,"verse":12},{"label":"Zch 13:2","book":"Zec","chapter":13,"verse":2},{"label":"2Tm 1:7","book":"2Ti","chapter":1,"verse":7},{"label":"Is 37:36–38","book":"Isa","chapter":37,"verse":36}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:37:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When the royal spokesman heard that the king of Assyria had pulled out of Lachish, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 10:31–32","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":31,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" he left and found him fighting against Libnah. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 33:20","book":"Num","chapter":33,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 10:29","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":29,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 10:31–32","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":31},{"label":"Nm 33:20","book":"Num","chapter":33,"verse":20},{"label":"Jos 10:29","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":29}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:37:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The king had heard concerning King Tirhakah of Cush, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 18:1","book":"Isa","chapter":18,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 20:5","book":"Isa","chapter":20,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" “He has set out to fight against you.” So when he heard this, he sent messengers to Hezekiah, saying, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 18:1","book":"Isa","chapter":18,"verse":1},{"label":"Is 20:5","book":"Isa","chapter":20,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:37:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Say this to King Hezekiah of Judah: ‘Don’t let your God, on whom you rely, deceive you "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 36:14–15","book":"Isa","chapter":36,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" by promising that Jerusalem won’t be handed over to the king of Assyria. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 36:14–15","book":"Isa","chapter":36,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:37:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Look, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all the countries: they completely destroyed them. Will you be rescued? "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:37:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Did the gods of the nations "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 36:18","book":"Isa","chapter":36,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" that my predecessors destroyed rescue them —Gozan, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 17:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 18:11","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":11,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" Haran, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 11:31","book":"Gen","chapter":11,"verse":31,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 12:1–4","book":"Gen","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 7:2","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":2,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" Rezeph, and the Edenites in Telassar? "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 36:18","book":"Isa","chapter":36,"verse":18},{"label":"2Kg 17:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":6},{"label":"2Kg 18:11","book":"2Ki","chapter":18,"verse":11},{"label":"Gn 11:31","book":"Gen","chapter":11,"verse":31},{"label":"Gn 12:1–4","book":"Gen","chapter":12,"verse":1},{"label":"Ac 7:2","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Isa:37:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, the king o